
1. Configure the python interpreter using "conda", with python version 3.8

2. Install the following packages under this url: https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/

    #"conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio cudatoolkit=10.2 -c pytorch"

    "conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio cudatoolkit=11.1 -c pytorch -c nvidia"

    Ignore the cudatoolkit for now, if the device does not have a cuda GPU, use this instead:
    "conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio cpuonly -c pytorch"

3. The resulting environment should have at least the following package with versions attached
Versions:

#pytorch-1.7.1
#torchvision-0.8.2-py36_cu102


4 Optional:
pip install opencv-python